text: Selma is a city in and the county seat of Dallas County, Alabama, United States, located on the banks of the Alabama River. The population was 17,971 at the 2020 census. The city is best known for the Selma to Montgomery marches, three civil rights marches that began in the city. ==Notable residents== *Jeff Sessions, U.S. Senator ==References== Category:County seats in Alabama
title: Selma, Alabama
